# 🔥 Pyforge Engine (Beta v0.2)

A blazing-fast, hybrid **C/OpenGL and Python** 2D game engine built for ultra-high-performance rendering. 

Unlike Pygame, which processes pixels sequentially on your CPU thread, Pyforge leverages low-level compiled C structures to pass matrix vectors directly to your graphics card's hardware acceleration layers (**GPU**), maintaining maximum frame rates even under massive sprite workloads.

---

## 🚀 Key Architectural Advantages
* **Hardware Accelerated:** Full OpenGL orthogonal viewport matrix operations out of the box.
* **Hybrid Core:** Blazing-fast math loops written in pure native C extensions.
* **Cross-Platform Fonts:** Automatically hooks into host operating system font databases (Linux, Windows, macOS) to render typographies seamlessly offline.
* **Intuitive API Design:** Clean, modern syntax tailored for developers, students, and indie engineers.

---

## 🛠️ Installation & Setup (Offline Beta Sandbox)

Compile the C source binaries and configure your isolated Python virtual environment instantly by using our automated lifecycle tools:

```bash
# Clean previous build caches and artifacts
make clean

# Recompile C extensions and initialize the virtual environment
make
```

To run your workspace game scripts instantly at any time, execute:
```bash
make run
```

---

## 📖 Quick Start API Reference Guide

### 1. Viewport Initialization
```python
import pyforge

# Opens a hardware-accelerated drawing canvas loop
pyforge.init(1024, 768, "My Custom Pyforge Game Window")
```

### 2. Automated Font Engines
```python
# Automatically scans the operating system (Windows/Mac/Linux) 
# and bakes a transparent character atlas sheet into VRAM seamlessly
pyforge.load_system_font("sans-serif", font_size=26)
```

### 3. Rendering Textures and Vector Shapes
```python
# Pre-calculates an n-sided regular polygon map layout
circle_mesh = pyforge.shape(36)
square_mesh = pyforge.shape(4)

# Loads an image file asset into VRAM completely offline
custom_sprite = pyforge.load_image("hero.png")

# Main Drawing Loop
while pyforge.is_open():
    # Clear screen frame with a gorgeous dual-color linear gradient blending
    pyforge.clear_gradient(top_color=(0.04, 0.04, 0.1), bottom_color=(0.12, 0.15, 0.25))
    
    # Renders your pre-calculated shapes anywhere with scaling and rotation matrices
    pyforge.drawshape(circle_mesh, x=512, y=384, size=80, angle=45.0, color=(0.2, 0.5, 0.9))
    
    pyforge.refresh()
```

### 4. Interactive HUD, Typography, and Mouse Tracking
```python
# Draws a flat, pixel-perfect layout panel box anywhere on your grid
pyforge.draw_button(40, 680, 180, 50, bg_color=(0.1, 0.5, 0.25))

# Prints actual string text directly inside your overlay dashboards
pyforge.draw_text("SCORE: 100", x=50, y=30, scale=0.6, color=(1.0, 0.85, 0.1))

# Live perimeter button hover & click detection math checks
mx, my = pyforge.get_mouse_pos()
if pyforge.is_button_clicked(40, 680, 180, 50):
    print("🟢 UI Action Button Perimeters Overlapped & Triggered!")
```

